ow lesbian and queer neighborhoods have folded under the capitalist influence of white, wealthy gentrifiers who have ultimately failed to make room for them. Nevertheless, they highlight the ways lesbian and queer communities have succeeded in carving out spaces-and lives-in a city that has consistently pushed its most vulnerable citizens away.Beautifully written, A Queer New York is an eye-opening account of how lesbians and queers have survived in the face of twenty-first century gentrification and urban development.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aGay people. 0aGays. 0aGender identity. 0aGender-nonconforming people. 0aIntersex people. 0aSexual minorities. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh  aBlack geographies.  aBrooklyn.  aConstellations.  aDisidentifications.  aFeminist theory.  aGentrification.  aGreenwich Village.  aLesbian.  aLines and orientations (Ahmed).  aManhattan.  aNeighbourhood.  aParadoxical space.  aPeople of color.  aProduction of space.  aQueer failure.  aQueer theory.  aQueers of color.  aRacism.  aTransgender and gender non-conforming people.  aUrban geography.  aWhiteness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Pack